Chinese authorities have strengthened anti-monopoly measures to create a healthier, competitive environment for the country's platform economy. This year, measures such as tightening competition supervision and law enforcement have been carried out. Â CGTN's Zhu Zhu interviews Zheng Junfang, chief risk officer of Alibaba Group, and Liu Xiangdong, former deputy director at the School of Financial Engineering University of Science and Technology Beijing, who both agreed that regulations to support the platform economy should be normalized to boost the sustainable development of the sector.